<br>
<p><i>The Northern Lights</i>, or Aurora Borealis, grace the Icelandic skies from late September to early April, painting a mesmerizing natural spectacle. Clear, remote locations away from city lights, such as the Golden Circle and Thingvellir National Park, offer optimal viewing opportunities. Monitoring the aurora forecast and joining Northern Lights tours with experienced guides can enhance your chances of witnessing this celestial ballet of colorful lights. deeply rooted in Icelandic culture and folklore.</p>
